%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.usnews.com%2Fnews%2Fpolitics%2Farticles%2F2021-02-14%2Fread-mcconnell-speech-after-trumps-impeachment-trial-acquittal%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20on%20the%20Senate%20floor%20in%202021%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20Trump%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-appeals-hearing-lawyer-argues-president-rival-assassinated-congress-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efacing%20those%20courts%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20criminal%20election%20interference%20case%20brought%20by%20Special%20Counsel%20Jack%20Smith.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20defense%20lawyer%2C%20D.%20John%20Sauer%2C%20argued%20before%20the%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20appeals%20court%20panel%20that%20a%20president%20cannot%20be%20criminally%20prosecuted%20for%20his%20actions%20in%20office%20if%20he%20wasn't%20impeached%20and%20convicted%20for%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20two%20of%20the%20judges%20noted%20that%20Trump%20had%20relied%20on%20the%20opposite%20argument%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20about%20the%20two%20concessions%20made%2C%20in%20the%20first%20impeachment%20proceeding%20and%20then%20in%20Trump%20v.%20Vance%2C%20that%20impeachment%20should%20be%20stayed%20and%20wait%20until%20he's%20out%20of%20office%20when%20he%20would%20be%20subject%20to%20criminal%20liability%3F%26quot%3B%20asked%20Judge%20Karen%20Henderson%2C%20a%20Republican%20appointee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESauer%20replied%20that%20the%20impeachment%20defense%20%E2%80%94%20which%20Smith's%20team%20also%20cited%20in%20its%20legal%20briefs%20%E2%80%94%20simply%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe%20have%20a%20judicial%20process%20in%20this%20country%2C%20period.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20did%20not%20say%20that%20we%20could%20never%20raise%20an%20immunity%20defense%26quot%3B%20in%20response%20to%20criminal%20prosecution%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJudge%20Florence%20Pan%20interjected%2C%20telling%20Sauer%20that%20Trump's%20defense%20lawyer%20in%2