.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20high%20court%20passed%20the%20order%20while%20upholding%20a%20family%20court%20order%20granting%20divorce%20to%20a%20man%20on%20the%20grounds%20of%20cruelty%20by%20his%20wife.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%2C%20also%20comprising%20Justice%20Neena%20Bansal%20Krishna%2C%20noted%20that%20the%20marriage%20between%20the%20couple%20was%20troubled%20from%20the%20beginning%20and%20the%20wife%20even%20consumed%20a%20mosquito%20repellent%20liquid%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20commit%20suicide%20but%20later%2C%20tried%20to%20wriggle%20out%20of%20the%20situation%20by%20claiming%20that%20she%20was%20compelled%20to%20do%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20woman%20alleged%20that%20since%20she%20was%20not%20being%20provided%20with%20a%20proper%20diet%2C%20she%20was%20administered%20the%20liquid%20by%20the%20husband%20on%20the%20pretext%20of%20it%20being%20a%20nutritious%20tonic%2C%20the%20court%20recorded%2C%20adding%20that%20she%2C%20however%2C%20subsequently%20accepted%20that%20her%20husband%20was%20at%20his%20place%20of%20work%20at%20the%20time%20of%20the%20incident.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSuch%20conduct%20of%20the%20appellant%20in%20attempting%20suicide%20and%20then%20trying%20to%20put%20the%20blame%20on%20the%20husband%20and%20his%20family%20members%20was%20an%20act%20of%20extreme%20cruelty%20as%20the%20family%20remained%20under%20the%20constant%20threat%20of%20being%20implicated%20in%20false%20cases%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20court%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20repeated%20threats%20to%20commit%20suicide%20and%20an%20attempt%20to%20commit%20suicide%20were%20held%20to%20be%20an%20action%20amounting%20to%20cruelty%20by%20the%20Supreme%20court....%20(In%20another%20case%2C)%20it%20was%20observed%20(by%20the%20top%20court)%20that%20in%20case%20the%20wife%20succeeds%20in%20committing%20suicide%2C%20one%20can%20only%20imagine%20how%20the%20poor%20husband%20would%20get%20entangled%20into%20the%20clutches%20of%20law%2C%20which%20would%20virtually%20ruin%20his%20sanity%2C%20peace%20of%20mind%2C%20career%20and%20probably%20his%20entire%20life.%20Such%20a%20threat%20of%20attempting%20suicide%20amounts%20to%20cruelty%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20court%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20further%20said%20although%20the%20wife%20has%20a%20legal%20right%20to%20take%20recourse%20for%20any%20wrong%2C%20making%20unsubstantiated%20allegations%20of%20having%20been%20subjected%20to%20dowry%20demands%20or%20acts%20of%20cruelty%20by%20the%20husband%20or%20his%20family%20members%20and%20getting%20criminal%20trials%20initiated%20against%20them%20are%20also%20%26quot%3Bclearly%20acts%20of%20cruelty%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20note%20that%20during%20the%20two%20years%20of%20their%20matrimonial%20life%2C%20the%20parties%20barely%20resided%20together%20for%2010%20months%20in%20all%20and%20even%20during%20that%20time%2C%20there%20were%20various%20acts%20of%20cruelty%20of%20being%20subjected%20to%20false%20complaints%20and%20civil%20as%20well%20as%20criminal%20litigation%20committed%20by%20the%20appellant%20(wife)%20towards%20the%20respondent%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20court%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%2C%20therefore%2C%20conclude%20that%20the%20learned%20additional%20principal%20judge%20of%20the%20family%20court%20has%20rightly%20held%20that%20the%20respondent%20was%20subjected%20to%20cruelty%20by%20the%20appellant%20and%20granted%20a%20divorce%20under%20section%2013(1)(ia)%20of%20the%20HMA%20(Hindu%20Marriage%20Act).%20We%20find%20no%20merit%20in%20the%20appeal%2C%20which%20along%20with%20the%20pending%20applications%2C%20if%20any%2C%20is%20hereby%20dismissed%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20court%20ordered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704810420000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2018-01%2Fdelhi-high-court_650x400_5