dom%20from%20January%208-10%2C%20the%20first%20Indian%20Defence%20Ministerial%20visit%20to%20the%20UK%20in%2022%20years%2C%20marks%20a%20significant%20improvement%20in%20bilateral%20ties%20and%20the%20building%20of%20trust%20despite%20differences%20over%20the%20Russia-Ukraine%20war.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYet%2C%20defence%20technological%20and%20industrial%20partnerships%2C%20a%20key%20objective%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20efforts%20to%20boost%20self-reliance%20in%20arms%20production%2C%20remains%20challenging%20with%20the%20reluctance%20of%20UK%20defence%20industry%20to%20engage%20boldly%20with%20India%2C%20unlike%20their%20counterparts%20in%20the%20US%20and%20France.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20January%202002%2C%20George%20Fernandes%2C%20the%20defence%20minister%20of%20an%20earlier%20BJP-led%20government%2C%20visited%20London%20amidst%20an%20India-Pakistan%20military%20crisis.%20Several%20junior%20defence%20ministers%20have%20visited%20since%20then%2C%20largely%20for%20defence%20and%20air%20shows.%20A%20planned%20visit%20to%20the%20UK%20in%20the%20summer%20of%202022%20by%20current%20defence%20minister%20Rajnath%20Singh%20was%20abruptly%20called%20off%20by%20India%20for%20%E2%80%98protocol%E2%80%99%20reasons.%20But%2C%20in%20effect%2C%20the%20Indian%20side%20felt%20they%20could%20not%20usefully%20engage%20with%20then%20UK%20Defence%20Secretary%20Ben%20Wallace%2C%20who%20perceived%20India%20as%20%E2%80%98not%20on%20side%E2%80%99%20on%20the%20Ukraine%20war.%20Since%20the%20appointment%20of%20his%20successor%20Grant%20Shapps%2C%20an%20inaugural%20meeting%20of%20the%20%E2%80%982%2B2%E2%80%99%20foreign%20and%20defence%20dialogue%20at%20Director%20General-level%2C%20took%20place%20in%20October%202023%20and%20the%20Defence%20Consultative%20Group%20meeting%20at%20Permanent%20Secretary-level%20was%20held%20in%20November%202023.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98Defence%20and%20Security%E2%80%99%20are%20one%20of%20five%20%E2%80%98pillars%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20India-UK%202030%20Roadmap%2C%20launched%20by%20prime%20ministers%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20Boris%20Johnson%20in%20May%202021%2C%20setting%20out%20a%20unique%20ten-year%20bilateral%20plan%20for%20prioritization%20and%20raising%20ties%20to%20a%20Comprehensive%20Strategic%20Partnership.%20During%20the%20meeting%20at%20the%20G20%20summit%20in%20New%20Delhi%20in%20September%202023%2C%20prime%20ministers%20Modi%20and%20Sunak%20agreed%20to%20build%20%E2%80%98a%20modern%20partnership%20in%20cutting-edge%20defence%20technology%2C%20trade%20and%20innovation%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20UK%20government%20supports%20India%E2%80%99s%20plans%20to%20develop%20its%20defence%20industry%2C%20which%20would%20reduce%20its%20dependence%20on%20Russian%20military%20equipment.%20In%20April%202022%2C%20it%20issued%20an%20India-specific%20open%20general-export%20license%20%E2%80%93%20the%20first%20given%20to%20an%20Indo-Pacific%20country%20%E2%80%93%20to%20permit%20exports%20of%20certain%20military%20and%20dual-use%20goods%20and%20technology.%20In%20September%202023%2C%20the%20UK%20launched%20a%20new%20organisation%20headed%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Defence%20called%20Defence%20Partnership%20India%20to%20build%20bilateral%20defence%20ties.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%2C%20in%20practice%2C%20no%20significant%20India-UK%20collaboration%20regarding%20defence%20capabilities%20has%20occurred%20as%20yet.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20reason%20for%20this%20is%20that%20its%20implementation%20depends%20on%20industry%20not%20government%2C%20marked%20by%20a%20notable%20lack%20of%20coordination%20and%20cooperation%20between%20the%20two.%20It%20is%20also%20affected%20by%20what%20an%20IISS%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EStrategic%20Comment%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20November%202023%20described%20as%20the%20%E2%80%98three-I%E2%80%99%20challenge%20for%20UK%20companies%20in%20relation%20to%20India.%20These%20pertain%20to%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20i)%20foreign%20investment%20%E2%80%93%20the%20absence%20of%20an%20Indian%20procurement%20category%20of%20majority%20foreign%20ownership%20for%20the%20most%20lucrative%20projects%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3Eii)%20intellectual%20property%20rights%20%E2%80%93%20the%20requirement%20for%20intellectual%20property%20for%20such%20projects%20to%20be%20Indian%20owned%20and%20controlled%3B%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3Eiii)%20indigenous-content%20requirements%20%E2%80%93%20a%20minimum%20level%20of%2050%25%20or%20more%20to%20be%20domestically-sourced%20for%20the%20parts%20and%20materials%20used%20in%20weapons%20or%20equipment.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20is%20also%20concern%20that%20sensitive%20technologies%20could%20be%20diverted%20from%20India%20to%20Russia%3B%20which%20the%20Indian%20government%20stoutly%20challenges.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftrade%2Findia-uk-trade-talks-not-stalled-indian-government-sources-deny-uk-newspaper-report%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98India-UK%20Trade%20Talks%20Not%20Stalled%E2%80%99%3A%20Indian%20Government%20Sources%20Deny%20UK%20Newspaper%20Report%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYet%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20defence%20minister%E2%80%99s%20visit%20could%20prove%20pivotal%20by%20progressing%20significant%20collaborative%20projects%20at%20a%20political%20level.%20The%20most%20important%20are%20the%20co-development%20and%20co-creation%20of%20gas-turbine%20propulsion%20technology%20by%20Rolls-Royce%20and%20India%E2%80%99s%20Defence%20Research%20and%20Development%20Organisation%20(DRDO)%20for%20the%20next-generation%20of%20Indian%20fighter-aircraft%20engines%2C%20where%20India%20will%20own%20the%20project%E2%80%99s%20most%20sensitive%20intellectual%20property%20as%20well%20as%20export-approval%20authority%3B%20the%20recent%20partnership%20for%20naval%20electric%20propulsion%20between%20the%20Indian%20government%20and%20GE%20(Naval)%2C%20UK%20as%20well%20as%20Rolls-Royce%3B%20and%20the%20procurement%20of%20ground-based%20air%20defence%20systems%20from%20MBDA%20(UK).%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20the%20Ministerial%20visit%20takes%20place%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20DRDO%20has%20shut%20down%20its%20office%20in%20the%20Indian%20High%20Commission%20in%20London%20and%20re-located%20its%20single%20official%20representative%20to%20France%3B%20and%20the%20Indian%20defence%20ministry%2C%20as%20part%20of%20a%20rationalisation%20process%2C%20has%20reduced%20its%20military%20representation%20in%20London%20from%20three%20one-star%20officers%20to%20a%20single%20officer.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAdditional%20challenges%20could%20include%20the%20emergence%20of%20firm%20evidence%20on%20allegations%20of%20official%20Indian%20involvement%20in%20targeted%20assassinations%2Fassassination%20attempts%20in%20the%20US%20and%20Canada%3B%20as%20well%20as%20a%20rise%20in%20Sikh%20separatist%20(Khalistani)%20extremism%20in%20the%20UK%20amidst%20upcoming%20general%20elections%20in%20India%20(in%20May-June%202023)%20and%20the%20UK%20(in%20the%20second%20half%20of%20the%20year)%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20finalised%20bilateral%20Free%20Trade%20Agreement.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ERahul%20Roy-Chaudhury%20is%20Senior%20Fellow%20for%20South%20Asia%2C%20the%20International%20Institute%20for%20Strategic%20Studies%20(IISS)%2C%20London.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704804320000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F09174855%2FScreenshot-2024-01-09-at-5.48.17.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fwhy-the-defence-ministers-visit-to-the-uk-could-be-pivotal%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22No%20significant%20India-UK%20collabo