01966%20World%20Cup%20final.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Beckenbauer%E2%80%99s%20seemingly%20untouchable%20legacy%20was%20indeed%20tarnished%20in%20his%20later%20years%20as%20his%20role%20in%20the%20awarding%20of%20the%202006%20World%20Cup%20to%20Germany%20came%20under%20scrutiny.%20In%202016%2C%20FIFA%E2%80%99s%20Ethics%20Committee%20opened%20an%20investigation%20into%20a%20dubious%20payment%20of%20%E2%82%AC6.7%20million%20(%247.45m)%2C%20allegedly%20authorized%20with%20Beckenbauer%E2%80%99s%20knowledge%2C%20to%20influence%20votes%20on%20FIFA%E2%80%99s%20Executive%20Committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuddenly%2C%20Germany%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9CSommerm%C3%A4rchen%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20the%20%E2%80%9Csummer%20fairy%20tale%2C%E2%80%9D%20as%20the%20historic%20World%20Cup%20summer%20became%20known%20%E2%80%93%20took%20on%20a%20darker%20hue%2C%20and%20Beckenbauer%20was%20one%20of%20the%20chief%20villains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENevertheless%2C%20despite%20the%20allegations%2C%20Beckenbauer%20will%20be%20accorded%20a%20place%20in%20the%20pantheon%20of%20football%E2%80%99s%20greats%20alongside%20Johann%20Cruyff%2C%20Afredo%20di%20Stefano%2C%20Ferenc%20Puskas%2C%20George%20Best%2C%20Eus%C3%A9bio%2C%20Pele%20and%20Diego%20Maradona.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20boy%20from%20Bavaria%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeckenbauer%20was%20born%20on%20September%C2%A011%2C%201945%2C%20in%20the%20ruins%20of%20post-war%20Munich%20and%20began%20his%20career%20at%20local%20side%20SC%201906%20Munich%2C%20before%20moving%20to%20Bayern%20Munich%20aged%2013.%20Just%20five%20years%20later%20on%20June%206%2C%201964%2C%20the%2018-year-old%20Beckenbauer%20made%20his%20debut%20for%20Bayern%E2%80%99s%20first%20team%20against%20Stuttgarter%20Kickers%2C%20a%20game%20in%20which%20he%20also%20scored%20his%20first%20goal%20for%20the%20club%20as%20Bayern%20went%20on%20to%20win%20promotion%20to%20the%20Bundesliga.%20German%20and%20European%20Cup%20Winners%E2%80%99%20Cup%20successes%20followed%20before%20Beckenbauer%2C%20now%20captain%2C%20led%20Bayern%20to%20their%20first%20Bundesliga%20title%20%E2%80%93%20and%20only%20their%20second%20ever%20German%20championship%20%E2%80%93%20in%201969.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%201970s%20would%20be%20Beckenbauer%E2%80%99s%20most%20successful%20decade%20as%20he%20led%20Bayern%20to%20three%20consecutive%20Bundesliga%20titles%20in%201972%2C%201973%20and%201974.%20The%20third%20was%20accompanied%20by%20the%20first%20of%20three%20consecutive%20European%20Cup%20wins%20%E2%80%93%20and%20a%20World%20Cup%20triumph%20on%20home%20turf%20as%20Beckenbauer%20captained%20West%20Germany%20to%20victory%20over%20the%20Netherlands.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F09153153%2FClKIM0hUkAEV5yW.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F09153153%2FClKIM0hUkAEV5yW.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F09153153%2FClKIM0hUkAEV5yW-300x168.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F09153153%2FClKIM0hUkAEV5yW-1024x573.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-692163%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22671%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EFranz%20Beckenbauer.%20Photo%3A%20X%2F%40beckenbauer%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGerman%20captain%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeckenbauer%E2%80%99s%20international%20career%20had%20begun%20nine%20years%20earlier%20in%20a%20World%20Cup%20qualifier%20against%20Sweden%20in%20Stockholm%20on%20September%2026%2C%201965%2C%20a%202-1%20win%20seeing%20Germany%20qualify%20for%20the%201966%20finals%20in%20England%2C%20where%20Germany%20lost%20in%20the%20final%20to%20the%20hosts.%20It%20was%20in%20that%20final%20that%20Beckenbauer%20and%20Charlton%20famously%20marked%20each%20other%20out%20of%20the%20game%2C%20such%20was%20the%20threat%20both%20posed%2C%20but%20Beckenbauer%20had%20still%20enjoyed%20a%20good%20tournament%20from%20an%20individual%20point%20of%20view%2C%20finishing%20third%20on%20the%20top-scorers%20list%20from%20a%20non-attacking%20position.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFour%20years%20later%20in%20Mexico%2C%20Germany%20took%20revenge%20on%20England%20as%20a%20stunning%20Beckenbauer%20goal%20inspired%20a%20comeback%20from%202-0%20down%20to%20knock%20out%20the%20reigning%20champions%20in%20the%20quarterfinal.%20Beckenbauer%20dislocated%20his%20shoulder%20in%20the%20semifinal%20defeat%20to%20Italy%20but%20continued%20to%20play%20on%20with%20his%20arm%20in%20a%20sling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20becoming%20captain%20of%20the%20national%20side%20in%201971%2C%20Beckenbauer%20led%20West%20Germany%20to%20victory%20in%20the%20European%20Championships%20in%201972%2C%20an%20achievement%20which%20saw%20him%20crowned%20European%20Footballer%20of%20the%20Year%20%E2%80%93%20only%20the%20second%20German%20to%20win%20the%20award%20after%20Gerd%20M%C3%BCller.%20When%20West%20Germany%20again%20reached%20the%20final%20four%20years%20later%2C%20this%20time%20losing%20on%20penalties%20to%20Czechoslovakia%2C%20Beckenbauer%20was%20named%20European%20Footballer%20of%20the%20Year%20for%20a%20second%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20finally%20lifting%20the%20World%20Cup%20in%201974%2C%20plus%20two%20more%20European%20Cups%20with%20Bayern%20in%201975%20and%201976%2C%20Beckenbauer%20became%20the%20first%20German%20player%20to%20move%20to%20the%20North%20American%20Soccer%20League%20(NASL)%20in%201977%20%E2%80%93%20although%2C%20with%20the%20German%20tax%20authorities%20on%20his%20case%2C%20the%20move%20also%20had%20private%20financial%20motives.%20Playing%20along%20Brazilian%20legend%20Pele%2C%20Beckenbauer%20won%20three%20NASL%20titles%20with%20the%20New%20York%20Cosmos%20and%20was%20inducted%20into%20the%20National%20Soccer%20Hall%20of%20Fame.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeckenbauer%20moved%20back%20to%20Germany%20in%20May%201980%2C%20joining%20Hamburg%2C%20with%20whom%20he%20won%20a%20fifth%20Bundesliga%20title%20in%201982.%20Over%20the%20course%20of%20his%20career%2C%20Beckenbauer%20played%20424%20Bundesliga%20games%2C%20396%20for%20Bayern%20and%2028%20for%20HSV.%20He%20finally%20hung%20up%20his%20boots%20in%201983%20after%20one%20final%20season%20in%20New%20York%2C%20before%20embarking%20on%20a%20career%20in%20management%20when%20he%20took%20over%20the%20German%20national%20team%20following%20a%20group-stage%20exit%20at%20the%201984%20European%20Championships%20in%20France.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBeckenbauer%20the%20coach%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20leading%20Germany%20to%20the%201986%20World%20Cup%20final%20against%20all%20expectations%2C%20Beckenbauer%20became%20only%20the%20second%20man%20to%20win%20the%20World%20Cup%20both%20as%20a%20player%20and%20a%20coach%20when%20Germany%20lifted%20the%20trophy%20at%20Italia%20%E2%80%9990.%20In%202018%2C%20Didier%20Deschamps%20also%20achieved%20the%20feat%20when%20he%20led%20France%20to%20victory%20in%20Russia.%20In%20club%20management%2C%20Beckenbauer%20won%20a%20French%20Ligue%201%20title%20with%20Olympique%20Marseille%20in%201991%20and%20the%20Bundesliga%20with%20Bayern%20Munich%20in%201994%2C%20before%20becoming%20club%20president%20from%201994-2009.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20his%20role%20at%20Bayern%2C%20Beckenbauer%20was%20also%20vice-president%20of%20the%20German%20Football%20Association%20(DFB)%20from%201998%20to%202010.%20It%20was%20in%20this%20capacity%20that%20he%20led%20the%20successful%20bid%20to%20host%20the%202006%20World%20Cup%2C%20a%20process%20which%20has%20since%20seen%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Ftime-runs-out-on-2006-world-cup-affair-trial%2Fa-53264879%5C%22%3EBeckenbauer%20embroiled%20in%20the%20cor