beyond%20that%20associated%20with%20the%20law%20of%20the%20land%3B%20it%20asserts%20the%20tenets%20of%20humanity%20and%20equality%20at%20a%20time%20these%20are%20becoming%20rare%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20newspaper%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%20of%20Justices%20B.V.%20Nagarathna%20and%20Ujjal%20Bhuyan%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-bilkis-bano-state-of-gujarat-remission-convict-246114%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20state%20of%20Gujarat%20%E2%80%9Cacted%20in%20complicity%20with%20the%20convicts%E2%80%9D.%20The%20top%20court%20said%20that%20the%20state%20government%20%E2%80%9Cacted%20in%20tandem%E2%80%9D%20with%20convict%20and%20breached%20the%20rule%20of%20law%2C%20usurped%20power%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20data-artid%3D%5C%2267719957%5C%22%20data-title%3D%5C%22Unlawful%20remission%3A%20On%20the%20Bilkis%20Bano%20case%20%5C%22%20data-url%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fopinion%2Feditorial%2Funlawful-remission-the-hindu-editorial-on-the-bilkis-bano-case%2Farticle67719957.ece%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20data-articleid%3D%5C%2267719957%5C%22%3EThe%20top%20court%E2%80%99s%20verdict%20quashing%20the%20orders%20releasing%2011%20men%20convicted%20for%20the%20heinous%20gang-rape%20and%20murder%20of%20several%20members%20of%20Bano%E2%80%99s%20family%20during%20the%20Gujarat%20pogrom%20in%202002%20is%20an%20%E2%80%9Cunequivocal%20indictment%20of%20the%20state%20government%E2%80%9D%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fopinion%2Feditorial%2Funlawful-remission-the-hindu-editorial-on-the-bilkis-bano-case%2Farticle67719957.ece%5C%22%3Ethe%20%3Cem%3EHindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20said%20in%20its%20editorial.%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20data-articleid%3D%5C%2267719957%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20ruling%20represents%20a%20blow%20for%20the%20rule%20of%20law%20and%20the%20restoration%20of%20faith%20in%20the%20judiciary%20at%20a%20time%20when%20there%20are%20doubts%20about%20the%20institution%E2%80%99s%20capacity%20to%20hold%20power%20to%20account%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20newspaper%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20data-articleid%3D%5C%2267719957%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20release%20of%20life%20convicts%2C%20who%20are%20generally%20expected%20to%20spend%20the%20entirety%20of%20their%20lives%20in%20prison%2C%20unless%20remission%20is%20granted%20after%20a%20prison%20term%20that%20should%20not%20be%20less%20than%2014%20years%2C%20ought%20to%20be%20individually%20considered%20and%20not%20part%20of%20any%20omnibus%20gesture%20without%20regard%20to%20the%20impact%20of%20their%20freedom%20on%20the%20victims%2C%20survivors%20and%20society.%20Any%20rational%20remission%20policy%20should%20encompass%20humanitarian%20considerations%20and%20the%20convicts%E2%80%99%20scope%20for%20reform%20without%20violating%20the%20rule%20of%20law%20or%20societal%20interests.%20In%20this%20case%2C%20none%20of%20the%20conditions%20for%20remission%20was%20met%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20data-articleid%3D%5C%2267719957%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cstrong%3EHindustan%20Times%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20data-articleid%3D%5C%2267719957%5C%22%3EThe%20reversal%20of%20remissions%20in%20the%20Gujarat%20riots%20case%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9Cwelcome%20corrective%20measure%E2%80%9D%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Feditorials%2Fjustice-for-bilkis-bano-101704724001768.html%5C%22%3Esaid%20%3Cem%3EHindustan%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20in%20its%20editorial.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20data-articleid%3D%5C%2267719957%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20reprieve%20enjoyed%20by%20these%20men%2C%20who%20were%20publicly%20felicitated%20in%20Gujarat%20on%20their%20release%2C%20was%20a%20blot%20on%20the%20justice%20system%20and%20cast%20a%20shadow%20even%20on%20the%20formidable%20record%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20which%20had%20ensured%20a%20fair%20closure%20for%20many%20riot%20victims%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20data-articleid%3D%5C%2267719957%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20its%20Monday%20%5BJanuary%208%2C%202023%5D%20order%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20said%20the%20remission%20was%20obtained%20through%20%E2%80%98fraud%E2%80%99.%20Clearly%2C%20due%20diligence%20was%20compromised%20by%20the%20government%20and%20the%20previous%20bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20itself.%20Remissions%20are%20not%20unusual%20in%20the%20case%20of%20life%20convicts%2C%20but%20they%20are%20rarely%20(if%20ever)%20extended%20to%20people%20convicted%20of%20heinous%20crimes%20such%20as%20murder%20and%20rape%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20newspaper.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20data-articleid%3D%5C%2267719957%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CBano%20and%20her%20family%20have%20been%20brave%20and%20relentless%20in%20pursuing%20justice%20%E2%80%93%20twice%20over.%20That%20should%20stay.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20data-articleid%3D%5C%2267719957%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Times%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20data-articleid%3D%5C%2267719957%5C%22%3ESaying%20that%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20need%20for%20policy%20safeguards%20in%20all%20cases%2C%20%3Cem%3ETOI%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20in%20its%20editorial%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fblogs%2Ftoi-editorials%2Fback-to-jail-sc-judgment-on-remission-in-bilkis-case-underlines-need-for-policy-safeguards-in-all-cases%2F%5C%22%3Enoted%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20%E2%80%9CRemission%20is%20integral%20to%20the%20justice%20system.%20But%20it%E2%80%99s%20important%20to%20ensure%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20a%20matter%20of%20political%20convenience.%20When%20SC%20concluded%20that%20Gujarat%20government%20usurped%20powers%20to%20order%20remission%2C%20the%20risks%20of%20the%20justice%20system%20being%20undermined%20by%20it%20were%20highlighted.%20Justice%20is%20poorly%20served%20not%20just%20by%20arbitrary%20detention%2C%20but%20also%20dubious%20remissions.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20data-articleid%3D%5C%2267719957%5C%22%3EIt%20said%20that%20this%20remission%20was%20%E2%80%9Ccontroversial%20on%20account%20of%20the%20horrific%20nature%20of%20the%20crime%20that%20led%20to%20the%20convicts%20being%20given%20life%20imprisonment%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704787291000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F09132719%2Fimage-1705.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Frestores-faith-in-judiciary-national-dailies-unite-in-praise-of-sc-verdict-on-bilkis-bano-case%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20ruling%20'asserts%20the%20tenets%20of%20humanity%20and%20equality%20at%20a%20time%20these%20are%20becoming%20rare'%2C%20said%20one%20of%20the%20editorials.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Frestores-faith-in-judiciary-national-dailies-unite-in-praise-of-sc-verdict-on-bilkis-bano-case%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Gunfight%20Continues%20in%20Manipur%E2%80%99s%20Moreh%2C%20Over%20200%20Villagers%20Forced%20to%20Leave%20Their%20Homes%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F31100356%2FGCm-A9Pa4AAS-Sn.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Security%20forces%20and%20militants%20clashed%20for%20the%20second%20consecutive%20day%20in%20Manipur%E2%80%99s%20border%20town%2C%20Moreh%2C%20on%20Monday%20(January%208).%20The%20exchange%20of%20fire%20has%20once%20again%20heightened%20tensions%20and%20caused%20panic%20among%20residents%20in%20the%20strife-torn%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreh%2C%20situated%20along%20the%20Myanmar%20border%2C%20had%20been%20on%20high%20alert%20following%20a%20series%20of%20attacks%20by%20militants%20on%20security%20forces%2C%20particularly%20targeting%20Manipur%20police%20commandos.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20gunfire%20initially%20erupted%20late%20on%20Sunday%2C%20with%20a