A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bhutan's%20Elections%20Are%20a%20Time%20to%20Recognise%20the%20Glory%20of%20Democracy%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F09104658%2F38483611462_4a890e6997_c.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20Bhutan%20enters%20the%20last%20stage%20of%20its%20fourth%20national%20elections%2C%20many%20observers%20%E2%80%93%20including%20many%20Bhutanese%20%E2%80%93%20are%20talking%20about%20the%20unhappiness%20in%20the%20%E2%80%9CHappy%20Kingdom%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20It%20is%20true%20that%20there%20is%20no%20shortage%20of%20problems.%20Bhutan%E2%80%99s%20economy%20is%20in%20a%20mess%2C%20its%20long-standing%20employment%20crisis%20is%20fuelling%20a%20migration%20of%20young%20out%20of%20Bhutan%2C%20and%20it%20is%20facing%20its%20most%20challenging%20external%20security%20environment%20in%20decades.%20But%20what%20is%20harder%20to%20see%2C%20is%20how%20successfully%20Bhutan%20has%20transitioned%20from%20an%20almost%20absolute%20monarchy%20into%20a%20vibrant%20and%20maturing%20democracy%20in%20the%20short%20time%20since%20its%20first%20national%20elections%20in%202008.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20scale%20of%20the%20transition%20is%20hard%20to%20grasp%20easily%2C%20which%20is%20one%20of%20the%20reasons%20that%20it%20is%20often%20overlooked.%20It%20was%20the%20third%20king%20of%20Bhutan%2C%20the%20dynamic%20Jigme%20Dorji%20Wangchuck%2C%20who%20established%20Bhutan%E2%80%99s%20National%20Assembly%20in%201953%20%E2%80%93%20barely%20a%20year%20into%20his%20reign%20from%201952%20to%201972.%20During%20this%20time%2C%20he%20transformed%20the%20country%3B%20freeing%20serfs%2C%20ushering%20in%20land%20reforms%2C%20and%20establishing%20the%20infrastructure%20that%20would%20transform%20the%20country%20from%20a%20subsistence%20economy%20to%20now%20having%20one%20of%20the%20highest%20per%20capita%20GDPs%20in%20the%20region.%20Nonetheless%2C%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20he%20gave%20the%20National%20Assembly%20the%20power%20to%20remove%20the%20king%20(a%20clause%20his%20son%2C%20the%20fourth%20king%2C%20would%20modify)%2C%20the%20country%20was%20an%20almost%20total%20monarchy.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESalman%20Haidar%2C%20who%20served%20as%20our%20Ambassador%20to%20Bhutan%20from%201980%20to%201983%2C%20said%20that%20the%20best%20understanding%20of%20the%20Bhutanese%20monarchy%20at%20that%20time%20was%20to%20view%20it%20as%20equivalent%20to%20the%20monarchies%20in%20Shakespearean%20plays.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20in%20%5Bthe%20play%5D%20Henry%20IV%2C%20for%20the%20fourth%20king%20%5BJigme%20Singye%20Wangchuck%5D%20the%20king%20and%20the%20country%20were%20one.%20Bhutan%20was%20what%20he%20was.%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20governance%20philosophy%20of%20Bhutan%2C%20and%20the%20pledge%20that%20most%20Bhutanese%20civil%20servants%20make%2C%20is%20to%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ETsa%20Wa%20Sum%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20or%20loosely%20to%20the%20king%2C%20country%2C%20and%20people%2C%20as%20one%20unit.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%202013%2C%202014%2C%202015%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pmo.gov.bt%2F%3Fpage_id%3D7055%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Estate%20of%20the%20nation%20addresses%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20by%20the%20second%20elected%20Bhutanese%20prime%20minister%2C%20Tshering%20Topgay%2C%20were%20titled%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20State%20of%20Tsa%20Wa%20Sum%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20deep%20association%20with%20the%20king%20and%20governance%20is%20what%20made%20the%20democratic%20transition%20so%20hard.%20Many%20Bhutanese%20felt%20the%20king%20was%20abandoning%20them%2C%20and%20they%20trusted%20him%20more%20than%20their%20own%20choice%20of%20people%20to%20govern%20them.%20Since%20education%20standards%2C%20health%2C%20life%20expectancy%2C%20wages%2C%20and%20well-being%20had%20all%20increased%20during%20the%20fourth%20king%E2%80%99s%20long%20reign%20(1972-2008)%20before%20his%20abdication%20in%20favour%20of%20his%20son%2C%20the%20current%20Druk%20Gyalpo%2C%20or%20king%2C%20Jigme%20Khesar%20Wangchuck%2C%20this%20was%20understandable.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20mock%20elections%2C%20held%20in%202007%2C%20to%20teach%20the%20people%20how%20to%20vote%2C%20there%20were%20four%20%E2%80%98stand-in%E2%80%99%20parties%20%E2%80%93%20Yellow%20for%20tradition%2C%20Green%20for%20sustainable%20ecology%2C%20Red%20for%20industrial%20development%2C%20and%20Blue%20for%20a%20fair%20and%20corruption-free%20society.%20Yellow%2C%20though%2C%20is%20also%20associated%20with%20the%20monarchy%20and%20monastic%20orders%2C%20and%20it%20was%20no%20surprise%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2FidUSDEL19868%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E46%20out%20of%2047%20constituencies%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20voted%20for%20Yellow.%20Covering%20the%20first%20real%20elections%20in%202008%2C%20it%20was%20hard%20to%20differentiate%20between%20the%20pledges%20of%20the%20Druk%20Phuensum%20Tshogpa%20(which%20won%20the%20elections)%20and%20the%20People%E2%80%99s%20Democratic%20Party.%20A%20Bhutanese%20friend%20explained%20it%20in%20the%20following%20way%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20PDP%20is%20royalist%20and%20traditionalist%2C%20and%20DPT%20is%20more%20royalist%20and%20more%20traditionalist.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20such%20things%20are%20easy%20to%20joke%20about%2C%20they%20were%20the%20principal%20hurdle%20for%20the%20democratic%20transition.%20Democracy%20is%20about%20the%20peaceful%20transition%20of%20power%2C%20based%20on%20the%20differing%20pathways%20that%20political%20parties%20offer.%20But%2C%20desperately%20afraid%20of%20criticising%20the%20royalist%20past%2C%20Bhutanese%20political%20parties%20did%20the%20opposite.%20Bhutan%20doubled%20down%20on%20what%20it%20had%20done%20in%20the%20past.%20Hydropower%2C%20which%20was%20the%20principal%20source%20of%20revenue%20for%20the%20country%2C%20was%20set%20to%20be%20expanded.%20High-end%20tourism%2C%20the%20second%20largest%20source%20of%20revenue%20and%20the%20highest%20employment%20sector%2C%20was%20expanded%20as%20well.%20The%20one%20piece%20of%20innovation%20%E2%80%93%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ipcs.org%2Fcomm_select.php%3FarticleNo%3D3963%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eminor%20outreach%20to%20China%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20by%20the%20first%20elected%20prime%20minister%2C%20Jigme%20Yoser%20Thinley%20%E2%80%93%20received%20such%20a%20strong%20backlash%20from%20India%2C%20that%20it%20is%20often%20seen%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dailyo.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbhutan-nepal-china-india-wen-jiabao-jigme-yoeser-thinley-lpg-narendra-modi-7331%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ewrongly%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E)%20as%20the%20main%20reason%20for%20him%20to%20lose%20the%202013%20elections.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20overcautious%20approach%20to%20the%20past%20has%20been%20costly%20for%20Bhutan.%20In%202008%2C%20Bhutan%20pledged%20to%20increase%20its%20hydropower%20capacity%20from%201%2C480%20MW%20to%2010%2C000%20MW%20in%202020.%20It%20has%20managed%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thethirdpole.net%2Fen%2Fenergy%2Fbhutan-failed-hydropower-goal-and-geopolitics-of-energy%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eonly%20increase%20it%20to%202%2C326%20MW%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20The%20huge%20projects%20are%20over%20budget%20and%20long%20delayed%2C%20adding%20to%20huge%20economic%20strain%20on%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20finances%2C%20since%20they%20are%20principally%20funded%20by%20loans%20from%20India.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20had%20a%20crippling%20impact%20on%20the%20tourism%20industry%2C%20and%20a%20ham-handed%20response%20by%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bhutantoday.bt%2Fexceeds-expectations-with-over-16000-visitors-since-reopening-despite-sdf-increase%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eincreasing%20the%20Sustainable%20Development%20Fee%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%202022%20across%20all%20sectors%20did%20little%20to%20help%2C%20leading%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ttgasia.com%2F2023%2F11%2F23%2Fbhutan-tourism-looking-bright-with-reduction-of-sustainable-development-fees%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E50%25%20reduction%20of%20the%20SDF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20by%20the%20end%20of%202023.%20The%20fixation%20on%20hydropower%20(with%20few%20jobs)%20and%20an%20unclear%20vision%20on%20tourism%2C%20has%20led%20to%20an%20exacerbation%20of%20a%20youth%20unemployment%20problem%2C%20which%20a%20worrying%20trend%20of%20Bhutanese%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fasia-pacific%2Fbhutans-jobs-woes-drive-an-exodus-australia-2023-07-28%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emigrating%20to%20places%20like%20Australia%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20And%2C%20on%20its%20border%2C%20with%20India%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20Bhutan%E2%80%99s%20principal%20security%20guarantor%20%E2%80%93%20unable%20or%20unwilling%20to%20manage%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fon-the-india-china-border-disengagement-is-not-resolution%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eoutcome%20of%20the%20Galwan%20imbroglio%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20Bhutan%20is%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.chathamhouse.org%2Fpublications%2Fthe-world-today%2F2023-12%2Fchina-takes-more-land-bhutan-expected-border-deal%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eincreasingly%20under%20pressure%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20accommodate%20Chinese%20claims%20on%20an%20unresolved%20border.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findia-china-doklam-real-problem-bhutan%5C%22%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20Real%20Problem%20Lies%20in%20its%20Bhutan%20Policy%2C%20Not%20the%20Border%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAll%20in%20all%2C%20it%20would%20seem%20to%20be%20that%20democracy%20has%20not%20brought%20much%20happiness%20to%20the%20Kingdom%20which%20coined%20the%20term%20Gross%20National%20Happiness%20(GNH).%20In%20fact%2C%20given%20that%20dissatisfaction%20is%20what%20leads%20people%20to%20vote%20out%20governments%2C%20the%20Bhutanese%20have%20well%20demonstrated%20their%20unhappiness.%20Bhutan%20has%20voted%20out%20every%20party%20that%20has%20won%20power%20%E2%80%93%20the%20DPT%20in%202013%2C%20the%20PDP%20in%202018%2C%20and%20the%20last%20governing%20party%2C%20and%20the%20Druk%20Nyamrup%20Tshogpa%20(DNT)%20which%20governed%20over%20the%20last%20five%20years%20has%20already%20been%20knocked%20out%20in%20the%20first%20round%20of%20the%20current%20elections.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGNH%20as%20a%20governing%20philosophy%2C%20though%2C%20has%20never%20been%20about%20this%20type%20of%20happiness.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDalip%20Mehta%2C%20who%20served%20as%20ambassador%20to%20Bhutan%20from%201995%20to%201998%2C%20was%20posted%20as%20junior%20diplomat%20in%20the%20country%20during%20the%201970s%2C%20when%20the%20fourth%20king%E2%80%99s%20term%20became%20well%20known.%20At%20that%20time%2C%20Mehta%20told%20me%2C%20the%20king%20was%20returning%20from%20an%20international%20conference%2C%20and%20was%20confronted%20by%20a%20pushy%20Indian%20journalist%20who%20asked%20him%20what%20it%20was%20like%20to%20rule%20a%20country%20with%20the%20lowest%20Gross%20National%20Product%20or%20GNP%20in%20the%20region.%20Irritated%2C%20the%20king%20had%20replied%20that%20it%20was%20more%20important%20that%20people%20were%20happier%20with%20the%20way%20they%20were%20going%2C%20that%20was%20the%20gross%20national%20term%20to%20be%20measured.%20Thus%2C%20GNH%20was%20born.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20frequent%20change%20in%20governing%20parties%20reveals%20the%20dissatisfaction%20with%20the%20solutions%20so%20far%20offered%2C%20it%20also%20reveals%20a%20deepening%20of%20democracy.%20In%20the%20first%20elections%2C%20only%20two%20parties%20qualified%20for%20elections%20%E2%80%93%20to%20run%20for%20an%20election%20a%20party%20has%20to%20have%20candidate%20from%20all%2020%20of%20its%20dzonkhags%2C%20or%20districts%2C%20of%20the%20country%20and%20all%2047%20National%20Assembly%20constituencies.%20This%20election%20there%20were%20five.%20Unlike%20the%20relatively%20empty%20slogans%20of%20earlier%20elections%2C%20now%20the%20candidates%20have%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkuenselonline.com%2Fseeded-candidates-present-dilemma-to-bartsham-shongphu-voters%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edetailed%20pledges%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20providing%20real%20%E2%80%93%20and%20tough%20%E2%80%93%20challenges%20for%20voters%20to%20make%20up%20their%20minds.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20A%20journalist%20friend%20of%20mine%2C%20also%20ran%20for%20elections%20this%20year%2C%20and%20although%20her%20party%20did%20not%20make%20it%20past%20the%20first%20round%20%E2%80%93%20the%20second%20round%20has%20a%20face-off%20between%20the%20two%20leading%20parties%20if%20no%20one%20party%20gets%20more%20than%2050%25%20of%20the%20vote%20share%20%E2%80%93%20the%20fact%20that%20young%2C%20idealistic%20people%20are%20willing%20to%20put%20in%20their%20life%20savings%20to%20make%20a%20difference%20through%20democratic%20means%20says%20a%20lot%20about%20the%20appeal%20of%20democratic%20politics%20in%20Bhutan.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20hard%2C%20these%20days%2C%20to%20be%20enthused%20by%20democracy.%20The%20power%20of%20money%2C%20the%20vanity%20and%20narcissism%20on%20social%20media%2C%20and%20global%20wars%2C%20make%20it%20difficult%20to%20trust%20that%20discussion%20and%20compromise%20can%20lead%20to%20good%20solutions.%20Bhutan%E2%80%99s%20story%20of%20deepening%20democracy%20becomes%20that%20much%20more%20important%20in%20this%20context.%20Against%20all%20odds%2C%20this%20country%20that%20had%20limited%20experience%20of%20elections%20and%20deliberative%20lawmaking%20except%20at%20the%20highest%20echelons%2C%20has%20embraced%20and%20committed%20itself%20to%20bettering%20itself%20through%20democratic%20means.%20Despite%20its%20many%20problems%2C%20its%20people%20have%20embraced%20a%20pathway%20that%20they%20had%20only%20once%20accepted%20reluctantly.%20Grumbling%2C%20dissatisfied%2C%20they%20are%20trying%20to%20find%20a%20pathway%20to%20progress%20together%2C%20in%20a%20manner%20they%20are%20(somewhat)%20happy%20with.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20can%20be%20no%20greater%20paean%20of%20praise%20to%20democracy%20or%20GNH%20both%2C%20than%20this.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EOmair%20Ahmad%20is%20an%20author%20and%20journalist.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704778358000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F09104658%2F38483611462_4a890e6997_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fbhutan-election-monarchy-happiness%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Despite%20the%20severe%20challenges%20that%20Bhutan%20faces%20%E2%80%93%20from%20its%20economy%20to%20its%20security%20%E2%80%93%20its%20stable%20and%20deepening%20democracy%20is%20one%20of%20the%20few%20bright%20spots%20in%20South%20Asian%20and%20global%20politics.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fbhutan-election-monarchy-happiness%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Six%20Things%3A%20Bilkis%20Bano%20Convicts%20Being%20Sent%20Back%20to%20Prison%20Is%20a%20Verdict%20on%20Much%20More%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F20123532%2FIMG_2186.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESpeaking%20of%20sending%20the%20convicted%2011%20back%20to%20jail%2C%20the%20resilient%20survivor%20of%20murderous%20attempts%20and%20gang%20rapes%20in%20the%202002%20Gujarat%20violence%2C%20Bilkis%20Bano%20has%20said%20she%20felt%20it%20was%20new%20year%20and%20she%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Ftoday-i-can-breathe-again-says-bilkis-bano-after-landmark-supreme-court-judgement%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ecould%20breathe%20again%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20The%20supreme%20court%20has%20allowed%20many%20to%20reaffirm%20their%20faith%20in%20the%20law%20of%20the%20land%20and%20the%20rule%20of%20law.%20%E2%80%9CI%20thank%20the%20honourable%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20for%20giving%20me%2C%20my%20children%20and%20women%20everywhere%2C%20this%20vindication%20and%20hope%20in%20the%20promise%20of%20equal%20justice%20for%20all%E2%80%9D%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20what%20other%20political%20significance%20does%20this%20landmark%20order%20have%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EReminder%20of%20where%20this%20government%20stands%20on%202002%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20immediately%20brought%20back%20the%20memories%20of%20the%20other%20heinous%20crimes%20committed%20in%20the%20name%20of%20avenging%20the%20burning%20of%20the%20train%20carrying%20%3Cem%3Ekarsevaks%3C%2Fem%3E%20from%20Ayodhya%20in%20the%20Sabarmati%20Express%20in%20Godhra%2C%2022%20years%20ago%20in%20February.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20The%20chief%20minister%20was%20then%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20having%20recently%20taken%20charge.%20The%20deaths%2C%20mayhem%20and%20destruction%20under%20his%20government%E2%80%99s%20watch%20put%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20politics%20on%20a%20polarised%20and%20charged%20path.%20On%20April%201%2C%202002%2C%20Justice%20(retired)%20J%20S%20Verma%2C%20then%20chairperson%20of%20the%20National%20Human%20Rights%20Commission%20(NHRC)%20noted%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fcities%2Fahmedabad%2Fas-nhrc-head-justice-verma-set-the-stage-for-justice-in-2002-riots%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Einvestigations%20in%20these%20cases%20were%20being%20%E2%80%9Cinfluenced%20by%20extraneous%20considerations%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20or%20players%20and%20recommended%20CBI%20probe%20into%20five%20cases%2C%20the%20Godhra%20carnage%2C%20killings%20at%20Gulberg%20Society%2C%20Naroda%20Patiya%2C%20Best%20Bakery%20in%20Vadodara%20and%20Sardarpura%20in%20Mehsana.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EReinforces%20why%20cases%20were%20shifted%20out%20of%20Gujarat%20and%20what%20has%20changed%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20spoke%20of%20fraudulent%20measures%20adopted%20by%20the%20state%20government%20to%20secure%20the%20May%202022%20order.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%20of%20Justices%20B.V.%20Nagarathna%20and%20Ujjal%20Bhuyan%20said%20that%20the%20state%20of%20Gujarat%20%E2%80%9Cacted%20in%20complicity%20with%20the%20convicts%E2%80%9D.%20The%20court%20said%20that%20the%20Gujarat%20government%20%E2%80%9Cacted%20in%20tandem%E2%80%9D%20with%20convict%2C%20breached%20rule%20of%20law%2C%20usurped%20power%E2%80%9D%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-bilkis-bano-state-of-gujarat-remission-convict-246114%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereports%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20Two%20cases%2C%20%3Cem%3EBest%20Bakery%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%3Cem%3E%20Bilkis%20Bano%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%94%20were%20moved%20out%20from%20Gujarat%20to%20Maharashtra.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Farticleshow%2F6249440.cms%3Futm_source%3Dcontentofinterest%26utm_medium%3Dtext%26utm_campaign%3Dcppst%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Times%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%20in%202010%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20how%20then%20chief%20minister%20Modi%20in%20a%20%E2%80%9Crabble-rousing%20speech%E2%80%9D%20that%20transfer%20of%20the%20case%20outside%20Gujarat%20%E2%80%9Cwould%20be%20an%20insult%20to%20the%20state%20as%20well%20as%20its%20judiciary.%E2%80%9D%20Turns%20out%20that%20the%20supreme%20court%20has%20noted%20in%202024%2C%20that%20%E2%80%9Cit%20was%20this%20very%20apprehension%20%5Bof%20acting%20in%20tandem%20with%20convicts%5D%20which%20led%20this%20Court%20to%20transfer%20the%20trial%20out%20of%20the%20State%E2%80%9D%20to%20Maharashtra.%20In%20matters%20of%20the%20when%20cases%20were%20shifted%20out%20of%20Gujarat%2C%20it%20was%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20which%2C%20through%20hearings%20and%20orders%20over%20the%20years%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fcities%2Fahmedabad%2Fgujarat-2002-cases-moving-key-riot-trials-out-to-indicting-state-what-supreme-court-once-said-and-did-7994865%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ecalled%20for%20%E2%80%9Cfair%20and%20impartial%20investigation%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20into%20the%20cases%20of%20violence%20in%202002.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESupreme%20Court%20verdict%20comment%20on%20BJP%20and%20Union%20government%20too%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20apex%20court%20also%20noted%20that%20if%20the%20convicts%20can%20%E2%80%9Ccircumvent%20the%20consequences%20of%20their%20conviction%2C%20peace%20and%20tranquillity%20in%20the%20society%20will%20be%20reduced%20to%20a%20chimaera.%E2%80%9D%20Gujarat%20has%20the%20same%20chief%20minister%20in%20office%2C%20Bhupendra%20Patel%20in%20May%202022%2C%20as%20it%20does%20now.%20The%20political%20dispensation%2C%20in%20effect%2C%20is%20the%20same.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Union%20home%20ministry%20had%20on%20August%2015%20last%20year%2C%20cleared%20the%20remission.%20The%20union%20government%20okayed%20whatever%20%E2%80%9Ccomplicity%E2%80%9D%20with%20convicts%2C%20the%20supreme%20court%20has%20noted%20in%20its%20order.%20PM%20Modi%2C%20who%20spoke%20of%20crimes%20against%20women%20in%20Congress-run%20Rajasthan%20last%20year%2C%20the%20Minister%20for%20Women%20and%20Child%20Welfare%2C%20the%20BJP%20Mahila%20wing%2C%20senior%20women%20ministers%20and%20Home%20Minister%2C%20Amit%20Shah%2C%20also%20an%20MP%20from%20Ahmedabad%20are%20absolutely%20quiet%20on%20this%20important%20matter.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Leaflet%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Erevealed%20last%20year%2C%20the%20Home%20Ministry%20okayed%20the%20remission%20of%20sentence%20to%20the%20guilty%2C%20issuing%20a%20letter%20to%20that%20effect%20on%20July%2011.%202023.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EHere%E2%80%99s%20the%20letter%20of%20the%20Union%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%20granting%20its%20approval%20to%20the%20premature%20release%20of%2011%20gang%20rape%20convicts%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FBilkisBano%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23BilkisBano%3C%2Fa%3E%20case.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FscYY8fxBza%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FscYY8fxBza%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20The%20Leaflet%20(%40TheLeaflet_in)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FTheLeaflet_in%2Fstatus%2F1582037729726332928%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EOctober%2017%2C%202022%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Nari%20vandan%E2%80%99%20under%20a%20dark%20cloud%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20is%20in%20stark%20contrast%20to%20what%20PM%20Modi%20spoke%20about%20women%20in%20his%20Independence%20Day%20speech%20last%20year.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20spoke%20of%20respecting%20women%2C%20women%20figured%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleasePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1948808%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E21%20times%20in%20his%20speech%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20The%20women%E2%80%99s%20reservation%20bill%2C%20though%20promising%20reservation%20in%20an%20indefinite%20future%2C%20involved%20talk%20of%20naari%20vandan%20(respecting%2Fpraying%20to%20women).%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EModi%20said%2C%20while%20introducing%20the%20bill%2C%20%E2%80%9CToday%2C%20God%20has%20given%20me%20the%20opportunity%20to%20take%20this%20forward%E2%80%A6Our%20Government%20is%20bringing%20a%20new%20Bill%20today%20on%20Women%E2%80%99s%20participation%20in%20both%20Houses.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Sanskari%20Brahmin%E2%80%99%20logic%20gets%20a%20reality%20check%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%2011%20convicted%20for%20the%20rape%20of%20Bilkis%20Bano%20and%20released%20by%20the%20Gujarat%20government%20are%20%E2%80%9CBrahmins%E2%80%9D%20and%20have%20%E2%80%9Cgood%20sanskaar%E2%80%9D%2C%20said%20the%20BJP%20MLA%20from%20Godhra%2C%20CK%20Raulji%20at%20the%20time.%20They%20were%20feted%20with%20sweets%20and%20garlands%20after%20their%20release.%20C.K.%20Raulji%20was%20also%20%E2%80%9Cone%20of%20the%20two%20BJP%20leaders%20who%20were%20part%20of%20the%20Gujarat%20government%20panel%20that%20unanimously%20decided%20to%20release%20the%20rapists.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20decision%20was%20taken%20after%20one%20of%20the%20convicts%20approached%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20seeking%20remission%20and%20the%20matter%20was%20passed%20onto%20the%20state%20government.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETook%20four%20gutsy%20women%20to%20push%20for%20justice%2C%20not%20the%20state%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20government%20at%20the%20state%20level%20and%20in%20the%20centre%20was%20one%20with%20the%20convicts%20on%20this%2C%20arguing%20for%20them%2C%20never%20speaking%20up%20for%20the%20survivor.%20It%20took%20women%20petitioners%2C%20expelled%20TMC%20MP%2C%20Mahua%20Moitra%2C%20ex-CPI(M)%20MP%2C%20Subhasini%20Ali%2C%20social%20worker%2C%20Revati%20Laul%20and%20Rooprekha%20Verma%20to%20petition%20the%20supreme%20court%20and%20move%20on%20Bilkis%20Bano%E2%80%99s%20behalf.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20The%20fact%20that%20it%20took%20independent%20women%20to%20fill%20in%20for%20the%20state%2C%20and%20stand%20up%20for%20the%20cause%20of%20justice%20for%20a%2021-year%20old%20Bilkis%20Bano%20in%202002%2C%20then%20five%20months%20pregnant%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2F2022%2F10%2F18%2Findias-modi-government-approved-release-of-bilkis-banos-rapists%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ewho%20survived%20gang%20rapes%2C%20the%20murder%20of%20her%20three-year%20old%20child%20and%20eight%20others%20in%20her%20family%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20as%20well%20as%20her%20unborn%20child%2C%20speaks%20volumes%20about%20the%20state%20of%20justice%20and%20women%E2%80%99s%20rights%20in%20India%20today.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704777830000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F20123532%2FIMG_2186.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fbilkis-bano-order-meaning-womens-rights-modi%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20order%20draws%20into%20focus%20the%20centre%E2%80%99s%20complicity%2C%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20silence%20on%20this%20and%20reminds%20India%20of%20why%20cases%20were%20shifted%20out%20of%20Gujarat.%20BJP%20MLA%E2%80%99s%20'sanskari%20Brahmin'%20remarks%20for%20convicts%20meets%20reality%20and%20shows%20that%20women%20need%20to%20push%20for%20justice%2C%20the%20state%20won%E2%80%99t.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A14%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fbilkis-bano-order-meaning-womens-rights-modi%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22French%20Prime%20Minister%20Elisabeth%20Borne%20Resigns%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F09093202%2FScreenshot-2024-01-09-at-9.31.57%25E2%2580%25AFAM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EFrench%20Prime%20Minister%20Elisabeth%20Borne%20resigned%20on%20Monday%20after%20less%20than%20two%20years%20in%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMs%20Elisabeth%20Borne%20today%20submitted%20the%20resignation%20of%20the%20government%20to%20the%20president%2C%20who%20accepted%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20presidency%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrench%20President%20Emmanuel%20Macron%20thanked%20her%20for%20%E2%80%9Cwork%20in%20the%20service%20of%20our%20nation%20that%20has%20been%20exemplary%20every%20day.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBorne%20said%20in%20her%20resignation%20letter%20that%20she%20and%20Macron%20agreed%20%E2%80%9Cit%20was%20more%20necessary%20than%20ever%20to%20push%20on%20with%20reforms.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%E2%80%99s%20next%20for%20Macron%E2%80%99s%20government%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBorne%20became%20the%20second%20female%20prime%20minister%20of%20France%20in%20May%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20resignation%20coincides%20with%20recent%20political%20tensions%20over%20contentious%20immigration%20legislation%20backed%20by%20Macron%20to%20enhance%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20deport%20some%20foreigners.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20that%2C%20Borne%20faced%20fierce%20criticism%20for%20bypassing%20parliament%20to%20push%20through%20unpopular%20pension%20reforms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20French%20system%2C%20the%20president%20sets%20general%20policies%20and%20appoints%20a%20prime%20minister%20to%20manage%20the%20day-to-day%20affairs%20of%20the%20government%2C%20meaning%20the%20latter%20is%20often%20held%20responsible%20when%20the%20administration%20faces%20turbulence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMacron%E2%80%99s%20office%20did%20not%20name%20a%20successor%20for%20Borne%2C%20but%20she%20will%20act%20as%20caretaker%20until%20a%20new%20government%20is%20named.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20amid%20days%20of%20intense%20behind-the-scenes%20manoeuvring%2C%20Education%20Minister%20Gabriel%20Attal%20appeared%20to%20emerge%20as%20the%20favourite%20to%20be%20France%E2%80%99s%20next%20prime%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20first%20appeared%20on%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Ffrench-prime-minister-elisabeth-borne-resigns%2Fa-67923725%5C%22%3EDW%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704773300000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F09093202%2FScreenshot-2024-01-09-at-9.31.57%25E2%2580%25AFAM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Felisabeth-borne-france-prime-minister%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Her%20resignation%20coincides%20with%20recent%20political%20tensions%20over%20contentious%20immigration%20legislation%20backed%20by%20Macron%20to%20enhance%20the%20government's%20ability%20to%20deport%20some%20foreigners.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Felisabeth-borne-france-prime-minister%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20We%20Can't%20Forget%20What%20the%20Modi%20Government%20Did%20to%20the%20Tablighi%20Jamaat%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F10%2F21113206%2Frepatriation.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20sometimes%20necessary%20to%20remind%20ourselves%20of%20the%20past%20in%20order%20to%20understand%20the%20present.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFour%20years%20ago%2C%20in%202020%2C%20evangelical%20Muslim%20organisation%20Tablighi%20Jamaat%20held%20a%20meeting%20in%20Delhi%20from%20March%2010%20to%2013.%20This%20was%20scheduled%20long%20before%20the%20onset%20of%20Covid-19%20and%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20was%20itself%20dismissive%20of%20the%20threat%20of%20a%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20March%2013%2C%202020%20PTI%20report%20had%20claimed%3A%20%E2%80%9CCovid-19%20is%20not%20health%20emergency%2C%20no%20need%20to%20panic%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Tablighi%20meeting%20was%20held%20before%20India%20issued%20guidelines%20on%20public%20gatherings.%20But%20as%20cases%20in%20India%20began%20to%20rise%20towards%20the%20end%20of%20March%2C%20the%20government%20determined%20it%20would%20scapegoat%20Muslims%20and%20enlisted%20the%20media%20to%20do%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20government%20made%20much%20of%20evacuating%20the%20area%20where%20the%20congregation%20was%20being%20held.%20The%20PM%20sent%20National%20Security%20Advisor%20Ajit%20Doval%20to%20%E2%80%9Creason%E2%80%9D%20with%20the%20organisers%2C%20who%20had%20been%20asking%20for%20safe%20evacuation%20for%20days.%20The%20virus%E2%80%99%20novelty%20and%20the%20first%20deaths%20coincided%20with%20the%20Tablighi%20Jamaat%20gathering%20and%20open%20season%20was%20declared%20on%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20main%20reason%20for%20increased%20number%20of%20cases%20is%20that%20members%20of%20the%20Tablighi%20Jamaat%20have%20travelled%20across%20the%20country%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Lav%20Agarwal%2C%20health%20ministry%20joint%20secretary.%20On%20April%201%2C%20BJP%20IT%20cell%20head%20Amit%20Malviya%20tweeted%20that%20the%20Tablighi%20gathering%20was%20like%20an%20%E2%80%9CIslamic%20insurrection%E2%80%9D.%20On%20April%204%2C%20MNS%20chief%20Raj%20Thackeray%20suggested%20the%20group%E2%80%99s%20members%20be%20shot.%20In%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20the%20group%E2%80%99s%20members%20were%20jailed%20and%20booked%20under%20the%20anti-terror%20National%20Security%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20April%205%2C%20Lav%20Agarwal%20said%3A%20%E2%80%98The%20doubling%20rate%20in%20India%20is%204.1%20days%2C%20had%20the%20congregation%20at%20Nizamuddin%20not%20happened%20and%20additional%20cases%20not%20come%2C%20this%20would%20have%20been%20about%207.14%20days.%E2%80%9D%20As%20later%20events%20proved%2C%20this%20was%20nonsense%2C%20but%20it%20was%20par%20for%20the%20course%20for%20this%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20April%2018%2C%20Agarwal%20made%20another%20claim%2C%20that%20the%20group%20was%20the%20dominant%20single%20cause%20of%20the%20pandemic.%20Thus%2C%20the%20poisonous%20lie%20was%20spread%20and%20its%20effect%20began%20to%20take%20place%20in%20the%20citizenry%20as%20fast%20as%20the%20COVID-19%20itself.%20A%20Hindi%20daily%20reported%20that%20Tablighi%20Jamaat%20members%20quarantined%20in%20a%20facility%20in%20western%20Uttar%20Pradesh%E2%80%99s%20Saharanpur%20had%20%E2%80%9Cdemanded%E2%80%9D%20non-vegetarian%20food%20and%20were%20defecating%20in%20the%20open%20inside%20the%20hospital.%20The%20Saharanpur%20police%20tweeted%20no%20such%20thing%20had%20happened%20and%20the%20story%20was%20taken%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Ftablighi-jamaat-communal-reporting-ib-ministry-coronavirus%5C%22%3ECOVID%2C%20Communal%20Reporting%20and%20Centre%E2%80%99s%20Attempt%20to%20Use%20Independent%20Media%20as%20Alibi%20for%20Inaction%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20months%20of%20active%20persecution%2C%20the%20group%E2%80%99s%20members%2C%20including%20foreigners%2C%20were%20jailed%2C%20charged%20with%20attempted%20murder%20and%20provisions%20of%20Section%20269%20(%E2%80%9Cwhoever%20wilfully%20or%20negligently%20does%20any%20act%20which%20is%20likely%20to%20spread%20the%20infection%20of%20any%20disease%20dangerous%20to%20life%E2%80%9D)%20were%20invoked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20theories%20being%20promoted%20were%20that%20they%20were%20deliberately%20spreading%20the%20virus%20around%20India%20by%20getting%20themselves%20infected%2C%20spitting%20on%20fruit%2C%20refusing%20to%20wear%20masks%2C%20running%20around%20naked%20in%20their%20wards%2C%20harassing%20nurses%2C%20and%20so%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENone%20of%20this%20was%20true.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20world%20noticed%20India%E2%80%99s%20malice%20against%20Muslims%20and%20it%20was%20reported%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20already%20dangerous%20to%20be%20Muslim%20in%20India.%20Then%20came%20the%20coronavirus%E2%80%9D%20(%3Cem%3ETIME%3C%2Fem%3E)%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CCoronavirus%3A%20Islamophobia%20concerns%20after%20India%20mosque%20outbreak%E2%80%9D%20(%3Cem%3EBBC%3C%2Fem%3E)%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20India%2C%20coronavirus%20fans%20religious%20hatred%E2%80%9D%20(%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3ENew%20York%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithout%20being%20convicted%20and%20even%20without%20any%20evidence%2C%20Jamaat%20members%20were%20%E2%80%9Cblacklisted%E2%80%9D%20from%20receiving%20visas%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Ftablighi-jamaat-covid-19-communalism%5C%22%3EThe%20Tablighi%20Jamaat%20Case%20and%20How%20India%20Topped%20a%20Global%20Index%20of%20Religious%20Bias%20During%20COVID%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20June%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%20amended%20the%20policy%20for%20visa%20applications%20to%20India%20to%20introduce%20a%20Tabligh-specific%20clause%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CRestriction%20on%20engaging%20in%20Tabligh%20activities%20%E2%80%94%20foreign%20nationals%20granted%20any%20type%20of%20visa%20and%20OCI%20cardholders%20shall%20not%20be%20permitted%20to%20engage%20themselves%20in%20Tabligh%20work.%20There%20will%20be%20no%20restriction%20in%20visiting%20religious%20places%20and%20attending%20normal%20religious%20activities%20like%20attending%20religious%20discourses.%20However%2C%20preaching%20religious%20ideologies%2C%20making%20speeches%20in%20religious%20places%2C%20distribution%20of%20audio%20or%20visual%20display%2Fpamphlets%20pertaining%20to%20religious%20ideologies%2C%20spreading%20conversion%2C%20etc%20will%20not%20be%20allowed.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20the%20first%20time%20in%20India%20that%20a%20particular%20religious%20group%20had%20been%20mentioned%20in%20the%20list%20of%20visa%20guidelines.%20This%20was%20purely%20to%20fuel%20the%20fire%20that%20was%20already%20raging%20in%20the%20media%2C%20blaming%20the%20group%20for%20the%20deliberate%20spread%20of%20COVID-19%20in%20India%20and%20absolving%20the%20government%20from%20its%20responsibility%2C%20especially%20for%20the%20fallout%20of%20the%20disastrous%20and%20unplanned%202020%20lockdown.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20only%20after%20it%20became%20generally%20accepted%20that%20the%20virus%20was%20an%20unstoppable%20global%20phenomenon%20which%20had%20spread%20through%20multiple%20ways%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9CTablighi%20conspiracy%E2%80%9D%20story%20faded.%20On%20May%2019%2C%20the%20foreign%20members%20of%20the%20Jamaat%20moved%20court%20to%20be%20released%20from%20institutional%20quarantine%2C%20where%20they%20had%20been%20held%20for%20over%20a%20month%20and%20a%20half%2C%20despite%20repeatedly%20testing%20negative%20for%20COVID-19.%20The%20government%20told%20the%20court%20that%20none%20of%20the%20visitors%20had%20been%20%E2%80%9Cdetained%E2%80%9D%2C%20they%20were%20merely%20%E2%80%9Casked%20to%20join%20the%20investigation%E2%80%9D.%20But%20the%20passports%20of%20over%20700%20Jamaat%20members%20had%20been%20seized%2C%20and%20they%20were%20not%20in%20fact%2C%20free.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Ftamil-nadu-detention-camp-tablighi-jamaat%5C%22%3ETamil%20Nadu%20Has%20Created%20a%20Detention%20Camp%20Just%20to%20Hold%20129%20Foreign%20Tablighi%20Jamaat%20Members%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20July%206%2C%20before%20the%20chief%20metropolitan%20magistrate%20at%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20Saket%20court%2C%2044%20Tablighi%20Jamaat%20members%20refused%20to%20pay%20fines%20of%20between%20Rs%204%2C000%20to%20Rs%2010%2C000%20in%20exchange%20for%20closing%20of%20cases%20and%20bravely%20chose%20to%20face%20trial.%20By%20December%2C%20eight%20months%20after%2011%20states%20had%20filed%2020%20FIRs%20against%20more%20than%202%2C500%20Tablighi%20Jamaat%20members%2C%20nobody%20was%20convicted.%20And%20the%20courts%20fiercely%20criticised%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20actions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJudges%20called%20the%20cases%20%E2%80%9Cmalicious%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Ca%20virtual%20persecution%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cabuse%20of%20process%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cabuse%20of%20power%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20said%20the%20Tablighi%20Jamaat%20members%20were%20%E2%80%9Cscapegoats%20of%20a%20political%20government%E2%80%9D%20who%20had%20acted%20against%20the%20group%20though%20having%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20an%20iota%20of%20evidence%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20such%20a%20vicious%20falsehood%20was%20allowed%20to%20be%20spread%20deliberately%20should%20tell%20us%20much%20of%20what%20we%20need%20to%20understand%20about%20where%20we%20are%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Faakar-patel%5C%22%3EAakar%20Patel%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20journalist%20and%20columnist.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704772716000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F10%2F21113206%2Frepatriation.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Ftablighi-jamaat-modi-lav-agarwal-covid-19%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22That%20such%20a%20vicious%20falsehood%20was%20allowed%20to%20be%20spread%20deliberately%20should%20tell%20us%20much%20of%20what%20we%20need%20to%20understand%20about%20where%20we%20are%20today.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A76%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Ftablighi-jamaat-modi-lav-agarwal-covid-19%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22New%20Research%20Raises%20Fresh%20Doubts%20About%20India%E2%80%99s%20River%20Linking%20Plans%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F12%2F10133535%2F2560px-Strong_rooted_in_the_middle_of_violent_Ken-2048x1153-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20October%20this%20year%2C%20the%20Indian%20forest%20department%20gave%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fpolitical-pulse%2Fken-betwa-river-linking-push-clear-project-mp-polls-8970586%2F%5C%22%3Efinal%20clearance%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0for%20a%20project%20to%20transfer%20water%20from%20the%20Ken%20river%20as%20it%20flows%20through%20the%20state%20of%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20to%20the%20nearby%20Betwa%20river.%20The%20Ken-Betwa%20river%20interlink%2C%20which%20would%20involve%20damming%20the%20Ken%20and%20laying%20a%20canal%20to%20the%20Betwa%2C%20is%20supposed%20to%20be%20the%20first%20of%2030%20proposed%20river%20interlinks%20which%20would%20fundamentally%20transform%20India%E2%80%99s%20river%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20original%20idea%20was%20conceptualised%20in%20the%2019%3Csup%3Eth%3C%2Fsup%3E%C2%A0century%20by%20Arthur%20Cotton%2C%20a%20British%20general%20and%20irrigation%20engineer.%20Cotton%20suggested%20connecting%20all%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20major%20rivers%20to%20enable%20better%20irrigation%20and%20navigation%2C%20and%20to%20capitalise%20on%20what%20was%20seen%20as%20the%20paradoxical%20phenomenon%20of%20having%20floods%20in%20one%20part%20of%20the%20country%20while%20other%20areas%20faced%20drought.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPost%20independence%2C%20despite%20official%20enthusiasm%20for%20large%20infrastructure%20projects%2C%20including%20hydropower%20dams%2C%20this%20particular%20approach%20did%20not%20gain%20any%20significant%20traction.%20In%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressreleaseshare.aspx%3FPRID%3D1777259%5C%22%3E1980%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0the%20Ministry%20of%20Irrigation%20(now%20subsumed%20under%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Jal%20Shakti)%20prepared%20a%20National%20Perspective%20Plan%20(NPP)%20%E2%80%9Cfor%20transferring%20water%20from%20water%20surplus%20basins%20to%20water-deficit%20basins%E2%80%9D%2C%20but%20no%20further%20government%20action%20followed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202002%2C%20however%2C%20A.P.J.%20Abdul%20Kalam%2C%20who%20was%20the%20President%20of%20India%20at%20the%20time%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnwda.gov.in%2Fcontent%2Finnerpage%2FILR-in-Supreme-Court.php%5C%22%3Emade%20a%20speech%20mentioning%20the%20subject%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Using%20the%20speech%2C%20Ranjit%20Lal%2C%20a%20senior%20lawyer%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20filed%20a%20public%20interest%20litigation%20in%20September%202002%2C%20and%20the%20court%20pronounced%20a%20judgement%20soon%20after%20asking%20for%20the%20project%20to%20be%20accelerated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDecisions%20made%20based%20on%20secret%20data%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202012%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20came%20back%20to%20the%20subject%20and%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F41857247%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520Writ%2520Petition%2520(Civil)%2520No%2Cissue%2520of%2520networking%2520of%2520rivers.%5C%22%3Edeclared%20in%20its%20judgement%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthese%20projects%20are%20in%20the%20national%20interest%2C%20as%20is%20the%20unanimous%20view%20of%20all%20experts%2C%20most%20state%20governments%20and%20particularly%2C%20the%20central%20government%E2%80%9D.%20But%20environmental%20experts%20who%20were%20consulted%20on%20the%20project%20as%20members%20of%20an%20expert%20committee%20set%20up%20as%20part%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20judgements%20have%20regularly%20raised%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fken-betwa-interlink-means-bundelkhand-will-suffer-for-decades-to-come%5C%22%3EKen-Betwa%20Interlink%20Means%20%E2%80%98Bundelkhand%20Will%20Suffer%20for%20Decades%20to%20Come%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHimanshu%20Thakkar%2C%20coordinator%20of%20the%20South%20Asia%20Network%20on%20Dams%2C%20Rivers%20and%20People%2C%20a%20network%20of%20activists%20working%20in%20the%20water%20sector%2C%20was%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Water%20Resources%E2%80%99%20expert%20committee%20on%20river%20interlinking%20from%202009%20to%202011.%20He%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Third%20Pole%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20while%20most%20of%20the%20committee%20members%20were%20government%20appointees%20who%20agreed%20with%20the%20project%2C%20independent%20experts%20like%20him%2C%20water%20management%20pioneer%20Rajendra%20Singh%20and%20watershed%20conservationist%20Vijay%20Paranjape%20often%20dissented.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20major%20issues%20for%20Thakkar%20was%20the%20use%20of%20secret%20hydrological%20data.%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20I%20asked%20for%20the%20data%20as%20a%20member%20of%20the%20expert%20committee%2C%20I%20was%20told%20that%20the%20Ken%20is%20part%20of%20the%20Ganges%20basin%2C%20an%20international%20basin%2C%20and%20%5Bsince%5D%20hydrology%20figures%20of%20international%20basins%20are%20a%20state%20secret%2C%20these%20cannot%20be%20made%20available%20%5Beven%20to%20the%20committee%20members%5D%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20hydrology%20data%20pertaining%20to%20the%20Ken%20basin%20and%20the%20Betwa%20basin%20is%20neither%20in%20the%20public%20domain%20nor%20has%20it%20ever%20undergone%20any%20independent%20public%20scrutiny.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20rainfall%20data%20of%20districts%20the%20Ken%20and%20the%20Betwa%20pass%20through%2C%20in%20the%20previous%20four%20years%20(2023%2C%202022%2C%202021%2C%202020)%2C%20is%20not%20appreciably%20different.%20So%20why%20has%20the%20Ken%20basin%20been%20categorised%20as%20having%20surplus%20water%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBhopal%20Singh%2C%20director%20general%20of%20the%20National%20Water%20Development%20Agency%20(NWDA)%20which%20is%20entrusted%20with%20the%20river%20linking%20project%2C%20disputes%20this.%20He%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Third%20Pole%3C%2Fem%3E%3A%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20project%20was%20based%20on%20detailed%20hydrological%20and%20simulation%20studies%20duly%C2%A0accounting%20%5Bfor%5D%20the%20upstream%2Fdownstream%20needs%2C%20environmental%20flows%2C%20etc.%2C%20in%20the%20Ken%20basin.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20hydrological%20studies%20were%20done%20by%20the%20National%20Institute%20of%20Hydrology%20(NIH)%2C%20Roorkee%2C%20and%20examined%20and%20reviewed%20by%20the%20Central%20Water%20Commission%2C%E2%80%9D%20Singh%20added.%20The%20NWDA%20website%20carries%20a%20detailed%20project%20report%20based%20on%20a%20NIH%20study%20conducted%20in%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fken-betwa-link-centre-moves-ahead-without-mandatory-latest-hydrological-study%5C%22%3E2003-04%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20the%20study%20itself%20is%20not%20included.%20Singh%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Third%20Pole%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20entire%20modelling%20cannot%20be%20shared%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fken-betwa-no-cost-analysis-or-environment-impact-study-structures-make-way-into-project%5C%22%3EKen-Betwa%3A%20No%20Cost%20Analysis%20or%20Environment%20Impact%20Study%2C%20Structures%20Make%20Way%20into%20Project%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20science%20may%20upturn%20old%20models%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20urgent%20issue%20is%20that%20science%20has%20moved%20a%20far%20pace%20from%20Cotton%E2%80%99s%20time%2C%20and%20the%20impact%20of%20interlinking%20rivers%20may%20be%20much%20more%20complicated%20than%20was%20appreciated%20in%20the%2019%3Csup%3Eth%3C%2Fsup%3E%C2%A0century.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESubimal%20Ghosh%2C%20institute%20chair%20professor%20at%20the%20Indian%20Institute%20of%20Technology%20Bombay%E2%80%99s%20Department%20of%20Civil%20Engineering%20and%20convener%20of%20the%20Interdisciplinary%20Program%20in%20Climate%20Studies%2C%20explained%20that%20atmospheric%20water%20has%20traditionally%20not%20been%20factored%20into%20consideration%20of%20water%20cycles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Farticles%2Fs41467-023-41668-x%5C%22%3Erecent%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0which%20Ghosh%20co-authored%20found%20that%20adjacent%20river%20basins%20do%20not%20exist%20in%20isolation%2C%20and%20moving%20water%20from%20one%20to%20another%20may%20have%20additional%20impact%20due%20to%20atmospheric%20water.%20The%20study%20builds%20on%20the%20fact%20that%20towards%20the%20end%20of%20the%20Indian%20summer%20monsoon%2C%20when%20the%20soil%20is%20saturated%20and%20evapotranspiration%20(the%20supply%20of%20moisture%20from%20the%20land%20to%20the%20atmosphere)%20is%20fairly%20high%2C%20recycled%20precipitation%20contributes%20to%20about%2025%25%20of%20monsoon%20rainfall.%20If%20water%20from%20one%20basin%20were%20to%20be%20used%20to%20irrigate%20another%20basin%2C%20the%20combination%20of%20increased%20evapotranspiration%20and%20wind%20could%20reduce%20the%20late%20monsoonal%20rain%20by%2012%25%20in%C2%A0some%20arid%20regions%20of%20the%20country%2C%20and%20increase%20rainfall%20up%20to%2010%25%20in%20other%20parts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNow%20we%20know%20for%20certain%20that%20altering%20the%20terrestrial%20water%20cycle%20can%20impact%20atmospheric%20processes%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Ghosh.%20He%20argued%20that%20there%20is%20%E2%80%9Can%20urgent%20need%20to%20include%20rigorous%20model-guided%20evaluation%20of%20hydro-meteorological%20consequences%E2%80%9D%20for%20projects%20like%20river%20interlinking.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%2C%20Singh%20of%20the%20NWDA%20said%20that%20they%20could%20not%20comment%20on%20a%20hypothetical%20study.%20%E2%80%9CConsidering%20the%20scale%20of%20meteorological%20and%20hydrological%20cycles%20in%20the%20country%2C%20these%20inter-basin%20water%20transfers%20to%20water-short%20areas%20are%20minor%20in%20nature%20%E2%80%A6%20As%20far%20as%20the%20Ken-Betwa%20link%20is%20concerned%2C%20the%20majority%20of%20harnessed%20flood%20water%20shall%20be%20utilised%20in%20the%20Ken%20basin%20itself%20and%20some%20water%20shall%20be%20utilised%20to%20fulfil%20the%20water%20needs%20of%20other%20regions%20including%20recharge%20of%20existing%20tanks%20in%20the%20Bundelkhand%20region%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F07%2F22145316%2FKen-the-wire.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F07%2F22145316%2FKen-the-wire.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F07%2F22145316%2FKen-the-wire-300x167.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F07%2F22145316%2FKen-the-wire-1024x571.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-541835%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22669%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EKen%20River.%20Photo%3A%20Dheeraj%20Mishra.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20illusion%20of%20water%20surplus%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20deeper%20problem%2C%20according%20to%20Thakkar%2C%20may%20be%20that%20the%20river%20basins%20classified%20as%20having%20a%20water%20surplus%20are%20only%20regarded%20as%20such%20because%20they%20are%20less%20developed.%20He%20pointed%20out%20that%20districts%20in%20the%20upper%20Ken%20basin%20are%20largely%20devoid%20of%20water-intensive%20agriculture%2C%20and%20with%20few%20dams%20built%20for%20storage.%20In%20contrast%2C%20the%20lower%20Betwa%20runs%20through%20agricultural%20districts%20where%20water-intensive%20crops%20are%20grown%2C%20with%20a%20fair%20number%20of%20dams.%20The%20surplus%2C%20he%20said%2C%20is%20only%20an%20illusion%20created%20by%20the%20different%20levels%20of%20water%20utilisation%20in%20different%20geographies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNow%20dams%20are%20sought%20to%20be%20built%20in%20the%20upper%20Betwa%20region%2C%20which%20will%20create%20a%20shortfall%20in%20the%20existing%20lower%20Betwa%20basin%20dams%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Thakkar.%20%E2%80%9CThat%20shortfall%20is%20proposed%20to%20be%20rectified%20by%20water%20from%20the%20Ken%20basin.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%2C%20Singh%20said%20that%20the%20Ken-Betwa%20link%20is%20not%20only%20about%20the%20inter-basin%20transfer%20of%20water%20%E2%80%93%20the%20central%20premise%20of%20river%20interlinking%20from%20Cotton%E2%80%99s%20time%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20decisions%20%E2%80%93%20but%20also%20about%20conserving%20flood%20water.%20Most%20rainfall%20occurs%20in%20a%20few%20days%20during%20the%20monsoon%2C%20and%20%E2%80%9Cthere%20are%20hardly%20any%20flows%20in%20the%20Ken%20during%20the%20non-monsoon%20period%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Singh.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20region%20is%20also%20not%20very%20rich%20in%20groundwater%20due%20to%20hard%20rock%20and%20marginal%20alluvium%20terrain.%20We%20expect%20this%20project%20to%C2%A0stabilise%20the%20availability%20of%20water%20and%20improve%20water%20management%20in%20the%20region%20particularly%20during%20drought%20years.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMajor%20downstream%20impacts%20of%20river%20interlinking%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESingh%E2%80%99s%20vision%20of%20the%20total%20utilisation%20of%20water%20raises%20its%20own%20issues%2C%20according%20to%20Depinder%20Kapur%2C%20director%20of%20the%20water%20programme%20at%20the%20Centre%20for%20Science%20and%20Environment%20in%20Delhi.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20more%20river%20waters%20we%20use%20for%20agriculture%20and%20irrigation%20and%20urban%20consumption%2C%20the%20less%20will%20be%20left%20to%20enter%20the%20sea%2C%20especially%20in%20peninsular%20India%20where%20rivers%20aren%E2%80%99t%20fed%20by%20Himalayan%20waters%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Kapur.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fonline.ucpress.edu%2Felementa%2Farticle%2Fdoi%2F10.1525%2Felementa.269%2F112824%2FRiver-linking-in-India-Downstream-impacts-on-water%5C%22%3E2018%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20if%20all%2030%20proposed%20river%20interlinking%20projects%20in%20the%20country%20are%20fully%20implemented%2C%20the%20average%20annual%20discharge%20by%20the%20affected%20basins%20will%20reduce%20by%2073%25.%20While%20the%20study%20focused%20on%20impacts%20to%20wetlands%20and%20estuaries%2C%20which%20would%20be%20deprived%20of%20key%20sources%20of%20water%2C%20there%20would%20also%20be%20major%20ramifications%20for%20the%20ocean.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fken-betwa-jal-shakti-secy-rejected-provisions-on-water-sharing-between-up-and-mp-citing-cost-hike%5C%22%3EKen-Betwa%20Link%3A%20Jal%20Shakti%20Secy%20Had%20Rejected%20Provisions%20on%20Water-Sharing%20Between%20UP%20and%20MP%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20significant%20fall%20in%20the%20flow%20of%20fresh%20river%20water%20into%20the%20sea%20would%20disrupt%20the%20upper%20layer%20of%20water%20in%20the%20Bay%20of%20Bengal%2C%20which%20is%20made%20up%20of%20low-salinity%20and%20low-density%20water%20that%20helps%20maintain%20a%20sea%20surface%20temperature%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fagupubs.onlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Fpdf%2F10.1029%2F2000JC000679%5C%22%3Ehigher%20than%2028%20degrees%20Celsius%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20high%20surface%20temperature%20in%20turn%20creates%20low-pressure%20areas%20and%20intensifies%20monsoon%20activity%2C%20explained%C2%A0Mihir%C2%A0Shah%3Cstrong%3E%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3Edistinguished%20professor%20at%20Shiv%20Nadar%20University%20and%20former%20chair%20of%20a%20new%20National%20Water%20Policy%20drafting%20committee%20set%20up%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Jal%20Shakti%20in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CRainfall%20over%20much%20of%20the%20%5BIndian%5D%20subcontinent%20is%20effectively%20controlled%20by%20this%20layer%20of%20low-salinity%20water.%20A%20disruption%20in%20this%20layer%20because%20of%20the%20massive%20damming%20proposed%20by%20the%20river%20interlinks%20%E2%80%A6%20could%20have%20serious%20long-term%20consequences%20for%20climate%20and%20rainfall%20in%20the%20subcontinent%2C%20endangering%20the%20livelihoods%20of%20a%20vast%20population.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERivers%20carry%20more%20than%20water%2C%20and%20sediment%20would%20also%20be%20held%20back%20by%20new%20dams%20built%20for%20river%20interlinking.%20This%20is%20a%20critical%20concern%20for%20the%20deltas%20of%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thethirdpole.net%2Fen%2Friver-basins%2Fganga%2F%5C%22%3EGanga%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%93%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thethirdpole.net%2Fen%2Friver-basins%2Fbrahmaputra%2F%5C%22%3EBrahmaputra%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Mahanadi%2C%20Godavari%2C%20Krishna%20and%20Kaveri%20basins%2C%20home%20to%20more%20than%20160%20million%20people%20who%20would%20be%20deeply%20impacted%20by%20sea%20level%20rise%20due%20to%20climate%20change.%20A%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Farticles%2Fs41467-023-38057-9%5C%22%3Enew%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20the%20Ganga-Brahmaputra%20Delta%20found%20that%20the%20approximately%201%20billion%20tonnes%20of%20sediment%20that%20rivers%20currently%20carry%20each%20year%20would%20increase%20by%2034-60%25%20in%20the%2021st%20century%20because%20of%20more%20monsoon%20rainfall.%20More%20sediment%20in%20the%20delta%20would%20help%20to%20offset%20sea%20level%20rise%20and%20naturally%20sustain%20the%20delta.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20as%20the%202018%20study%20pointed%20out%2C%20if%20all%20dams%20involved%20in%20the%20proposed%20river%20interlinking%20projects%20are%20built%2C%20this%20sediment%20load%20would%20fall%20by%2087%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESingh%20of%20the%20NWDA%20responded%20by%20saying%20that%20sediment%20trapping%20by%20reservoirs%20and%20their%20impact%20on%20deltas%20was%20%E2%80%9Calways%20exaggerated%20without%20proper%20scientific%20study%E2%80%9D.%20While%20suggesting%20that%20such%20impacts%20would%20be%20%E2%80%9Cnominal%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20told%20The%20Third%20Pole%20that%20the%20NWDA%20had%20%E2%80%9Calready%20initiated%20system%20studies%20of%20the%20proposed%20link%20projects%20to%20study%20the%20likely%20impact%20of%20climate%20change%20on%20hydrology%20and%20water%20availability%2C%20demand%20patterns%2C%20surface%20and%20ground%20water%20interactions%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELooking%20ahead%2C%20with%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20having%20returned%20to%20power%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20in%20the%20November%202023%20elections%2C%20and%20with%20river%20interlinking%20having%20been%20featured%20in%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%202019%20general%20election%20manifesto%2C%20it%20seems%20likely%20that%20work%20on%20the%20Ken-Betwa%20link%20will%20be%20prioritised%20as%20evidence%20of%20the%20plan%20making%20progress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ECharu%20Bahri%20is%20a%20freelance%20writer%20and%20editor%20based%20in%20Rajasthan.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thethirdpole.net%2Fen%2Fnature%2Fnew-research-raises-fresh-doubts-about-indias-river-linking-plans%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoriginally%20published%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20The%20Third%20Pole.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22publi